{"word":"ἐκθύω","slug":"ἐκθύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκθύω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ύσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to offer up, sacrifice, slay</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to atone for, expiate by offerings</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>lustrare, expiare</el>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; but <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to propitiate, appease</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}